The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | HDFC duo slash deposit rates
                                                                                                               HDFC duo slash deposit rates
                                          
	Mumbai, June 18 (PTI): Housing Development Finance Corporation Limited has reduced deposit rates by up to 25 basis points across various maturities with immediate effect.        
	Indias second largest private sector lender, HDFC Bank, has also reduced its deposit rates by up to 25 basis points. The reduction will be effective from tomorrow, HDFC Banks executive director, Paresh Sukthankar, said.        
	This reduction is in line with the market trends and taking into account the developments happening in the market in the recent past, he said.        
	A host of lenders, including the countrys largest bank, the State Bank of India, and second largest lender ICICI Bank, had recently reduced their deposit rates.        
	While ICICI Bank had effected the reduction by 25-50 basis points across select maturities last month, the SBI slashed deposit rates by 25 basis points in all tenures effective from June 15.         
	It is the second cut in deposit rates by the SBI within a month.        
	On May 13, it had cut rates by 25-50 basis points. Since April, it had cut deposit rates of various maturities by 75-100 basis points.                                                                                                                                                         
